<TEXT>
cesar gaviria trujillo who wants to 
eliminate drug trafficking end government corruption and help the 
poor was easily leading in the presidential primary of the 
governing liberal party according to election results late monday 
besides the presidential primary colombians also chose a 
congress mayors city councilmen and state assemblies in sundays 
elections 
presidential elections take place may 26 
with 43 percent of the total vote counted the national 
elections office said gaviria had 1310000 votes or 48 percent of 
the total cast for all six liberal party presidential candidates 
in second place was former bogota mayor hernando duran with 636593 
votes or 23 percent third was sen ernesto samper with 488297 
votes or 18 percent 
vote tallying was delayed because the computer system broke 
down and counting proceeded by hand in this south american country 
of 30 million people 
the major radio networks rcn and caracol said exit polls 
indicated two former guerrillas won mayoral contests in small towns 
gaviria was campaign manager of sen luis carlos galan a 
popular presidential candidate who was slain in bogota last aug 18 
by drug traffickers 
with the only other major contender the conservative party 
weakened by infighting and represented by rodrigo lloreda 47 who 
has failed two previous attempts to be president there is little 
doubt gaviria will be elected 
at 43 gaviria would be colombias youngest president ever 
the choice of the liberal partys presidential candidate was the 
most important part of the elections as colombia faces threats from 
drug traffickers leftist guerrillas and right wing death squads 
samper and the other liberal party contenders for the 
presidential nomination had indicated they wanted to negotiate with 
drug traffickers and end the 6monthold war between drug barons 
and government security forces 
one liberal party presidential aspirant alberto santofimio who 
took the most vigorous antius position called for an end to the 
war against traffickers 
gaviria acknowledged late sunday that his probable victory 
stemmed from galans popularity he promised to follow galans 
program of attempting to wipe out drug trafficking 
however he suggested he may prefer to try drug traffickers in 
colombia rather than send them to the united states for trials 
something the traffickers fear greatly 
gaviria also promised to follow galans programs for a more 
equitable justice system which usually favors the wealthy and 
influential and to try to create more schools jobs housing and 
better living conditions for the poor 
previous colombian presidents have not given much importance to 
solving problems of the poor failure to face those problems has 
resulted in rapid growth of leftist guerrilla insurrection 
it was the first time the liberal party leaders did not choose 
the presidential candidate usually the choice is based upon 
reports from local powerbrokers who show they can deliver votes 
according to exit polls by networks the liberal party appeared 
to have won 60 percent of the seats in the 313member congress the 
conservative party appeared headed for 37 percent of the seats 
while leftist parties are expected to win 3 percent rcn and 
caracol said 
currently congressional seats have a breakdown of 57 percent 
liberal and 37 percent conservative with the balance held by 
leftists 
former leftist guerrillas of the april 19 movement appeared to 
have won two of the 1005 mayoral races rcn and caracol said 
the group known as the m19 surrendered its weapons last week 
in an impressive ceremony that marked the first time a guerrilla 
organization voluntarily ended its violence in colombias three 
decades of armed insurrection 
there are five other guerrilla groups none of which reached 
peace terms with the government 
juan caicedo a liberal was elected mayor in the capital 
bogota a city of 6 million people according to the radio reports 
president virgilio barco ends his fouryear term aug 7 by law 
he is ineligible to run for a second consecutive term 
</TEXT>
