<TEXT>
a high school art teacher shot his wife and 
daughters to death as they slept monday then killed himself 
authorities said 
grade school principal dean collins asked the sheriffs office 
to check on the family when joe pianalto 33 didnt report for 
work and his daughters annie 8 and jennifer 6 didnt report to 
school 
sheriff don panzer said he found shirley pianalto 35 dead in 
her bed with a gunshot wound to the back of the head the children 
were in their bed also dead of head wounds 
pianaltos body was behind the girls bed a hunting rifle at 
his side panzer said the teachers wound appeared to be 
selfinflicted the sheriff said 
the county coroner dr leo meduna estimated that the deaths 
occurred between 3 am and 4 am monday 
everybody is just absolutely horrified about what has taken 
place here panzer said what were trying to find out is what 
possibly could have triggered him to do such a thing 
the family moved to this northcentral kansas town about 35 
miles northwest of salina three or four years ago 
the last homicide in this rural community of about 1600 people 
occurred in 1977 when a missouri fugitive held a couple and their 
teenage son hostage for several hours before shooting them and 
killing himself panzer said 
