<TEXT>
they fought and suffered they saw 
their comrades killed and wounded and their own lives crippled by 
bullets or bombs now they feel their sacrifice and achievement are 
going unrecognized 
dona violeta talks about everyone but us complained 
commandante wilmer a regional chief of the contra insurgency 
based in the hills here on the border with nicaragua 
nicaraguan presidentelect violeta barrios de chamorro along 
with president daniel ortega has called for the contras to 
disband but the contras want more they want credit 
were the ones who created the conditions for dialogue among 
the central american presidents wilmer said of last years 
regional summit meetings the talks produced sandinista concessions 
on early elections and international scrutiny 
wilmer like other contras argues that the sandinistas made 
concessions only because they wanted to get rid of the pressure of 
the contra resistance although ussupported the current contra 
leadership maintains it is a homegrown insurgency that grew out of 
conditions created by the sandinistas inside nicaragua 
mrs chamorro leading a 14party alliance trounced ortega in 
the feb 25 vote that grew out of the peace process she is to take 
office april 25 
we have to be paid the respect due men who have spilled our 
blood each combatant has to know his effort has not been for 
nothing said wilmer who uses only his nomdeguerre 
the contras were defeated militarily but now feel they deserve 
credit for what turned out to be a political victory 
well return to nicaragua when were respected as combatants 
as part of the victory said jackson another young 
commandante 
asked what kind of appreciation the contras want to see from 
mrs chamorro wilmer said they would like to praised in a speech 
but it cant be limited to just words the words should be backed 
up with deeds 
he said the combatants most of whom are peasant farmers are 
not looking for government positions or handouts but they will 
need financial help to rebuild their lives back home 
wilmer 27 years old and a veteran of nine years of 
counterrevolution is a prime example of the new breed of contra 
chief the movements leadership was overhauled last year at the 
insistence of men like him who spent years in the mountains 
fighting a war that killed an estimated 30000 people 
the businesssuited contra honchos who spent most of their time 
lobbying in washington miami and tegucigalpa were pushed out 
the field commanders viewed those leaders the ones the us 
public saw posing with ronald reagan or testifying in congress 
for the most part as venal politicians insensitive to the needs and 
objectives of the fighting man 
wilmer and the members of the revamped command spend most of 
their time at this sprawling camp home for the past two years to 
about 10000 fighters and 42000 dependents a few thousand contra 
combatants operate inside nicaragua where wilmer spent several 
months prior to his return to yamales in late february 
about 3000 rebel soldiers gathered on a parade ground thursday 
to hear an address from commander ruben the top contra after 
chief of staff israel galeano known as franklin 
ruben told the troops that in the nottoodistant future they 
would parade into managua to the cheers of a thankful throng 
but just when or how the contras will demobilize and what will 
become of them after they do has emerged as the major stumbling 
block to a peaceful transition in nicaragua 
the sandinistas insist the rebel army must disarm and disband 
before inauguration day 
