<TEXT>
poor bonn for 41 years this sleepy 
city on the banks of the rhine has been trying to live down its 
image as one of europes least exciting capitals 
now west germanys leaders are talking about making berlin the 
capital of a united germany and bonn residents are worried about 
the future 
my customers are politicians and the whole periphery around 
them chauffeurs secretaries and tourist groups who come to see 
the government area said juergen rausch whose family has run a 
newspaper kiosk across from parliament since west germanys 
creation in 1949 
among rauschs betterknown customers are chancellor helmut kohl 
and foreign minister hansdietrich genscher 
the main source of my income would disappear if bonn were no 
longer the capital said rausch 
bonn birthplace of beethoven has many qualities 
farm tractors occasionally clank along major streets in bonns 
suburbs barges ply the rhine and people stroll on pathways along 
the easymoving river 
its a homey place in many ways theres the maternus 
restaurant for example whose owner drags out photo albums to show 
customers pictures of some of her famous guests including ronald 
reagan kohl and genscher 
a stone statue of beethoven broods over muensterplatz the 
citys quiet cobblestoned main square just a couple blocks away 
from the colorful daily farmers market 
bonn university a former 18thcentury palace with majestic 
onionshaped domes is widely respected in the fields of science 
political science history and law wolfgang paul who shared the 
nobel prize for physics with two others last year teaches and 
studies atoms at the university 
but its not fun city 
bonn has never been able to cast off its image as a provincial 
capital on saturday nights as many say the nightlife is a 
20minute autobahn drive away in cologne 
bonn is half the size of a chicago cemetery and twice as 
dead goes one old joke 
bonns image isnt helped much by uninspired government 
buildings that lack the grandeur of structures in london or paris 
bonn has 290000 residents counting politicians government 
workers bureaucrats and diplomats who live in the city because it 
is the capital berlin germanys seat of government from 1871 
until 1945 is a vibrant cosmopolitan city of 18 million 
berlin became a key hanseatic league trading center in the 14th 
century and later the seat of powerful prussian kings it emerged 
as a center of german national feeling after the napoleonic wars 
and rose to become one of the worlds great cities before the 1933 
nazi takeover 
unlike bonn berlin has many famous monuments and architectural 
treasures like the former reichstag building and brandenburg gate 
bonn has been a standin capital since 1949 with the idea that 
when german unification occurs berlin would regain the capital 
crown it lost as a result of the third reichs defeat and germanys 
postwar separation 
now with heady talk of reunification west germanys leaders 
have been saying the capital of a united germany rightfully belongs 
in berlin 
berlin is the city in which the heart and for which the 
heart of the germans beats says genscher 
the indivisible german nation must also have its heart in the 
right place that is berlin he recently told the welt am 
sonntag newspaper 
a recent poll indicated nearly threefourths of all west germans 
favor installing the capital of a united germany in berlin there 
have been no similar polls for people in east germany whose 
capital is already east berlin 
despite the popular support for berlin as capital some 
opposition politicians have said bonn should retain the title 
partly because of berlins past as the center of hitlers third 
reich 
for 12 years berlin was the capital of the brutal hitler 
dictatorship says freimut duve federal lawmaker with the 
opposition social democrats 
no one has yet formally proposed making berlin a united 
germanys capital 
and with all the complications of unification and berlin 
technically still under the control of four foreign powers the 
united states britain and france making berlin the capital could 
take some time 
government officials say billions of dollars of construction and 
remodeling work already begun in bonns government quarter will be 
completed but have left open whether plans for further projects 
will ever get off the ground 
kohl has said he would like to see berlin the capital again but 
hints that bonn could keep some crucial federal government 
responsibilities 
i am for berlin but bonn must keep important functions he 
was quoted as saying by the bild newspaper last month 
that kind of talk is worrying bonn boosters 
a group of bonn merchants selfemployed workers and scholars 
has already launched a yes to bonn lobbying campaign to keep 
their city as a united germanys capital 
they have been saying that while berlin is tainted by the nazi 
years west germanys 41 years of democracy have bloomed in bonn 
west german news media say bonn could lose nearly half its 
residents if the capital is moved to berlin and real estate prices 
in bonn have already begun to slip 
bonn city officials seem to be putting their hopes on hints by 
kohl and others that their city wont be completely forsaken 
we are just at the beginning of the capital city question 
says mayor hans j daniels 
