les aspin the chairman of the house armed 
services committee says his plan for next years pentagon budget 
is in the back of his beadyeyed mind and hes not talking 
the wisconsin democrat says he plans to hide in the weeds 
while others are wrestling with the issue of us defense spending 
in a world where the perceived threats to the nation are changing 
with breathtaking speed 
