the 1980s were a decade in which defense spending accelerated 
rapidly and then leveled off near 300 billion a year the yearly 
budget battle took on a comfortable script the republican 
administration would propose a big increase the democrats would 
pare it down and a compromise would be struck 
that pattern has now been shattered by the developments in the 
soviet sphere 
its a confusing situation it changes the way the game is 
played said rep leon panetta dcalif chairman of the house 
