the white house proposed a small increase in pentagon spending 
for fiscal 1991 less than what it would take to keep pace with 
inflation but enough to protect cherished programs such as the b2 
stealth bomber and the strategic defense initiative its a 
comfortable position for congressional republicans of whom defense 
secretary dick cheney was one until last year 
