priorities they now have to decide how deeply to cut from cheneys 
303 billion request and where the cuts will be made 
panetta says the toughest decisions will be on terminating 
weapons programs especially those such as the b2 bomber where 
significant investments have been made and where budget savings are 
slow to be realized 
what youre talking about is reversing the process which took 
place in the last eight years where the military could launch 
