soviet union in nearly 30 years soviet sources say 
lis trip scheduled to begin april 23 or 24 follows the 
dramatic visit to beijing by soviet president michael s gorbachev 
last may that ended three decades of bad blood between the two 
communist neighbors 
the exchange of visits however has come against a background 
of swiftly unfolding events that largely eliminated fears or 
expectations that a sinosoviet rapprochement would transform world 
strategic alliances 
gorbachevs visit was overshadowed by studentled prodemocracy 
demonstrations in beijing that led to a violent military crackdown 
in june and the ascendancy of a new hardline leadership 
lis trip comes at a time of radical political and economic 
changes in the soviet union that have again dislocated any 
ideological compatibility the two sides might have had 
although china has not openly criticized the soviet union 
senior leader deng xiaoping in internal speeches has reportedly 
accused gorbachev of revisionism a word used by mao tsetung 
in condemning nikita khrushchev in the 1950s 
disputes between mao and khrushchev over ideology and leadership 
of the communist world led to a final break in 1960 when the 
soviets withdrew all their technical advisers from china 
the last chinese premier to visit moscow was chou enlai who 
attended a soviet party congress in october 1961 chou avoided 
meeting khrushchev blasted his policy of detente with the west and 
scorned the soviet leader by laying a wreath on the tomb of his 
discredited predecessor stalin 
li who studied engineering at the moscow power institute from 
1948 to 1954 is said to speak russian and has long been identified 
with sovietstyle central planning and stress on heavy industry 
in december 1985 thenvice premier li made a surprise stopover 
in moscow on his way home from a european tour for a meeting with 
gorbachev to promote warming relations between the two countries 
the 61yearold premier has denied however that he is 
prosoviet and his talks in moscow are not expected to produce any 
