<TEXT>
two mild aftershocks to the upland 
earthquake shook parts of los angeles and san bernardino counties 
early today but no injuries or damages were reported 
seismologists said 
the first aftershock at 326 am measured 33 on the richter 
scale and the second at 329 am measured 28 said robert finn 
of the california institute of technology in pasadena both were 
centered four miles northwest of upland he said 
upland police received about 20 telephone calls from residents 
who reported feeling the aftershocks but lt john cannon said no 
injuries or damages were reported 
the feb 28 upland earthquake measured 55 on the richter scale 
and caused nearly 13 million in damages according to a 
preliminary estimate by the state office of emergency services 
the richter scale measures ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs an earthquake of magnitude 2 is the smallest normally 
felt by humans while a quake of magnitude 3 can cause slight 
damage a magnitude 5 quake can cause considerable damage 
