<TEXT>
the entire communist party 
leadership resigned today in response to opposition demands and the 
leader of the longtime soviet client state said the ruling party 
must renew itself to head off crisis 
the fiveman politburo of the mongolian peoples revolutionary 
party voted to abolish the constitutional clause declaring the 
party the leading force in society 
it also set april 10 as the date for a special party congress to 
elect a new central committee that in the words of party general 
secretary zhambyn batmonh should be younger and in favor of reform 
the politburo voted to hold early elections this year for the 
new legislature the great peoples hural an exact date was not 
set 
the moves were obvious concessions to protesters who crowded the 
central square of the capital ulan bator on friday to demand 
change in the partys leadership and an emergency party congress 
the demonstrations shown on soviet television were evidence 
that the winds of democratic change that swept through eastern 
europe last year have reached asia mongolia is a sparsely 
populated nation on the sovietchinese border 
the mongolian democratic union an organization similar to the 
grassroots citizens groups that have sprung up in the soviet union 
is demanding an end to the communist partys 69yearold monopoly 
on power a mutiparty system and resignation of the premier 
cabinet and legislature 
it has also called for new elections and for the withdrawal of 
soviet troops 
two years ago mongolias leaders followed the lead of soviet 
president mikhail s gorbachev and embarked on political and 
economic reforms but critics say it has been moving too slowly 
batmonh announced the politburo decision in a speech to the 
120member central committee that was broadcast live he also said 
he was giving up his no 1 job in the party though mongolian 
officials did not rule out the possibility that those who resigned 
might be reelected 
as chairman of the hurals presidium batmonh is also mongolias 
head of state and that job was not affected by todays 
announcement 
the politburo decisions must be approved by the central 
committee but all are expected to pass the committee which began 
meeting after the politburo session will continue its meeting on 
tuesday 
batmonh said the partys main task is to build human and 
democratic socialism on the soil of mongolia it is important to 
renew our party leadership with younger people people who are 
clever and constructive and for perestroika 
he said the party should be the leading force in society but 
should acquire that status by its work and not from a 
constitutional article 
we also recognize the main principle of marxismleninism 
batmonh added national unity and stability are very important 
for perestroika 
a foreign ministry official said the next step after the 
central committee approves the politburo measures will be 
establishment of a commission to prepare for the april party 
congress batmonh said this commission could include younger 
reformminded members 
one of the tasks of the new hural once elected will be to 
approve a new constitution work on the draft has already started 
one of the goals of the new constitution will be to separate the 
roles of party and government 
batmonh said the draft for new party rules already being worked 
on internally should be published and discussed widely 
the central committee has received many letters from ordinary 
workers and party organizations he said some scientists sent 
an open letter to the central committee and worked out a draft 
program for party renewal 
he said all of these suggestions were being considered 
the party is ready to have active cooperation and negotiations 
with every force that is for democracy socialism and improving the 
welfare of our people the mongolian leader said the mongolian 
peoples revolutionary party will fight against forces that are 
against the interests of the people and extremist organizations 
batmonh also called for renewed effort to rehabilitate people 
wrongly punished in past political purges 
there was a bad tradition that those who criticized the 
leaders of the party were punished he said he said this 
tradition should be eradicated and any possibility of a cult of 
personality reemerging should be ruled out 
