and that the proposal would for the first time establish a clear 
balance of power between the legislative and executive branches of 
government 
gorbachev in his present post holds executive authority while 
also presiding over the congress of peoples deputies and the 
supreme soviet 
lukyanov also pointed out a presidential veto could be 
overridden by a twothirds majority of both houses of the supreme 
soviet legislature which is similar to the us presidents veto 
power and while the soviet president would have power to declare 
war lukyanov said the president would be required to immediately 
solicit the determination of the supreme soviet 
the new office must be created by a constitutional amendment 
which requires a twothirds majority of all deputies not just 
those voting 
a boycott by a substantial number of deputies therefore could 
torpedo the proposal 
