the united states and other western nations have never 
recognized the soviet unions forcible annexation of lithuania and 
its baltic neighbors while under red army occupation the three 
states once part of czarist russia had gained independence after 
world war i 
in 1940 a year after the infamous nonaggression pact between 
stalins soviet union and hitlers germany the soviet army imposed 
regimes that rubberstamped the three republics incorporation into 
the soviet union 
the baltic states were overrun by hitlers nazi troops and 
subject to terror and death camps and terrorized again by stalins 
secret police after the red army recaptured the lands more than 1 
million people perished in the baltic states during world war ii 
fitzwater in a written statement said the united states 
believes it is in the mutual interest of lithuania the soviet 
union and all csce countries to resolve this issue peacefully we 
call upon the soviet government to address its concerns and 
interests through immediate constructive negotiations with the 
government of lithuania 
the csce is the 3nation conference on security and cooperation 
in europe also known as the helsinki process it includes all the 
nations of europe except albania and also the united states and 
canada 
the helsinki process which produced paneuropean agreements on 
arms control and human rights in 1975 is now regarded as a way to 
help shape the new europe in the wake of the dramatic shifts toward 
democracy across the east bloc 
