<TEXT>
soviet troops boarded trains and 
headed for home monday the first to leave hungary as part of an 
agreement to remove all red army soldiers from the country by june 
30 1991 
a military band played the soviet and the hungarian national 
anthems as the first contingent of 300 troops and 37 combat 
infantry vehicles pulled out moscow has 49700 troops in hungary 
the withdrawal began just two weeks after the kremlin began 
bringing home troops from neighboring czechoslovakia where a 
similar agreement was reached last month on the removal of all 
73500 soviet soldiers there 
moscow has committed itself to remove the last of its troops and 
equipment from both countries by june 30 1991 
not many hungarians turned out in this tiny village station to 
see off the red army soldiers 
i am just glad to see them go said miklos szilasi an 
elderly resident i saw them come and ill really believe it only 
when the last one leaves 
soviet troops have been in hungary since the end of world war 
ii they are mainly associated with the bloody crushing of the 1956 
uprising for more democracy and a multiparty system 
moscow agreed to withdraw its troops in the initial days of the 
revolt but instead of departing reinforcements poured in to crush 
the uprising 
the start of the withdrawal comes just two weeks before 
hungarians go to the polls march 25 for the first free multiparty 
elections since the communists consolidated power in 1948 
some opposition leaders have said the new government might try 
to renegotiate the withdrawal agreement with moscow to move forward 
the completion date 
as the troops boarded the trains and combat vehicles were 
fastened to flatbed rail cars activists from the opposition league 
of young democrats held up banners reading hurry home sunny 
azerbaijan awaits you a sarcastic reference to kremlins 
dispatching soldiers to quell ethnic strife in the soviet caucasus 
they should leave as fast as they came in said zsuzsa 
szelenyi 
the withdrawal agreement was signed in moscow on saturday by 
soviet foreign minister eduard shevardnadze and his hungarian 
counterpart gyula horn 
i think that the overwhelming majority of our people wanted to 
see this agreement said ferenc somogyi the no 2 in the foreign 
ministry who negotiated the agreement and who came to this town 75 
miles southwest of budapest to see the first troops off 
addressing the oppositions concern that the withdrawal be 
accelerated somogyi said we considered it of crucial importance 
to get the pullout under way without delay i do not exclude the 
possibility of shortening the deadline but we think it is a tight 
one 
he noted the agreement stipulates that the withdrawal must be 
completed before june 30 1991 
maj gen viktor shilov first deputy to the commanderinchief 
of the southern group of forces stationed in hungary said the 
pullouts will now be a daily event from various parts of hungary 
by the end of this year 70 percent of the combat forces will be 
withdrawn 
somogyi said the soviet evaluation of 1956 is still to come 
hungary would like to see an admission by moscow concerning its 
role in 1956 similar to the apology extended to prague for the 1968 
sovietled warsaw pact invasion that crushed reforms there 
shilov noted it is good to be a guest but it is even better 
to go home 
some guests 45 years said an old peasant under his breath 
</TEXT>
