the mayor of tokyo in 1912 temperatures ranging from the mid 60s 
to the upper 80s are expected for the rest of the week 
the earliest the trees have ever blossomed was march 20 but 
forecasters say it could be even earlier this year the delicate 
pink and white blossoms last four to five days after they peak 
if things go according to our estimates by april 1 the 
program may just be the japanese tree festival because the 
blossoms will have come and gone national weather service 
meteorologist jim belleville said 
about 1300 of the trees ring the tidal basin between the 
lincoln and jefferson memorials with the rest planted on nearby 
park land 
forecasters said there was still hope that the cooling effect of 
the nearby potomac river could slow down blossom development 
temperatures near water are always lower than those farther away 
from water belleville said 
