a strong earthquake struck the north 
pacific on monday and was felt 110 miles away in the aleutian 
island town of adak 
there are no reports of damage or injury 
the quake had a preliminary strength of 62 on the richter 
scale said alec medberry at the tsunami warning center in palmer 
it was not strong enough to generate a tsunami or tidal wave 
he added 
the quake struck at 541 am ast and was centered about 110 
miles southeast of adak 
medberry said it was also felt in the aleutian island town of 
atka about 100 miles away 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one means a tenfold increase in 
magnitude 
an earthquake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage 
