<TEXT>
a congress of ethnic estonians on 
monday demanded an exact deadline for ending the occupation and 
illegal annexation of the republic of estonia as the first step 
toward restoring its independence 
the parliament of another soviet baltic republic lithuania 
declared its independence from the soviet union on sunday 
estonia has no need to do that because this land of 16 million 
residents is already an independent though occupied country said 
tunne kelam a leader of the movement to create the congress 
trivimi velliste a founder of the citizens movement declared 
we want moscow now to recognize the expression of the will of the 
estonian people our main aim is to establish our legal position of 
an occupied country 
estonians are using different tactics from the lithuanians to 
restore the statehood both enjoyed between the world wars because 
only 60 percent of its population is ethnic estonian the rest are 
largely russians who have migrated to the area since it was 
forcibly annexed in 1940 and many of them prefer to remain part of 
the soviet union 
lithuania is still 80 percent lithuanian and support there for 
independence is overwhelming 
estonian activists registered 700000 ethnic estonians who last 
month elected 465 representatives to the new congress which 
convened over the weekend activists say this organization is the 
true legislature not the supreme soviet parliament that will be 
elected sunday by all the soviet citizens of estonia 
the twoday session that ended monday demanded that moscow 
withdraw all soviet troops and immediately cease kgb activity in 
estonia the group also wants soviet military bases abolished 
velliste said the soviet union has 150000 soldiers in estonia 
or about one of every 10 people he said more are coming here as 
they are withdrawn from eastern europe 
some of them are situated only 50 kilometers 31 miles east 
of tallinn and forced to camp out in tents for lack of space he 
said 
velliste said his group would be willing to negotiate on troop 
withdrawal 
a declaration that described all state authorities of the 
estonian soviet socialist republic as only administrative organs 
for the occupation was read out to tumultuous applause 
however the congress voted to restore good neighborly relations 
with the soviet union on the basis of mutually beneficial 
cooperation and respect for each others rights 
velliste said estonians do not fear the consequences 
he asked what else can they do to us we have experienced 
everything we have experienced mass deportations and killings in 
the stalinist regime 
congress delegates elected a 78member council to conduct talks 
with moscow and foreign nations for recognition of complete 
independence 
the congress has the sole legitimate power now in estonia the 
supreme soviet will have no official position said kelam who is 
expected to be elected council chairman 
however delegates said the new 105member supreme soviet 
parliament to be elected next sunday would play a role in 
cooperating with the council in the transition period 
after we get guarantees from moscow about the withdrawal of 
troops we will hold parliamentary elections and form the first 
democratically elected government of an independent estonia 
velliste said in an interview 
we shall have that government by the end of 1991 maybe even 
sooner 
volunteers guarded the congress entrance after a breakin at 
congress headquarters and purported attempts by members of the 
largely russian group interfront to sabotage the meeting 
fortythree nonvoting members at the congress represented 
35000 nonestonians who said they want to be citizens of 
independent estonia when the new government is established 
