<TEXT>
new president patricio aylwin pledged 
respect for human rights monday in a speech to a huge gathering 
celebrating the rebirth of democracy in chile but indicated he 
will avoid holding trials for past abuses 
singing flagwaving sometimes weeping chileans packed the 
82000seat national stadium five miles southeast of downtown 
santiago to hear aylwin a site that long served as a dark symbol 
of bloody political repression 
aylwin a 71yearold centrist christian democrat became 
president sunday ending 16 years of authoritarian rule by 
rightwing gen augusto pinochet 
on seizing power in a violent 1973 coup pinochet launched a 
harsh antileftist campaign thousands of suspected dissidents were 
rounded up and brought to national stadium where human rights 
groups say many were tortured and some were executed 
aylwin appeared on monday to rule out vigorous prosecution and 
punishment of military officers for abuses committed during 
pinochets rule 
he remarked at mondays evening rally that in sorrowful days 
of blind and hateful predominance of force over reason it the 
stadium was a place of confinement and torture for many 
compatriots 
from this place we say to all chileans and the world that 
is watching us never again never again violations of human 
dignity 
aylwin promised to clarify the truth about the disappearances 
of people the horrendous crimes and other grave human rights 
violations that occurred during the dictatorship 
but he called for tempering the virtue of justice with the 
virtue of prudence and said a time for forgiveness would 
come 
chile he said must avoid becoming engulged indefinitely in 
inquiries recriminations and witchhunts 
the issue is seen as one of the most politically sensitive to be 
faced by aylwins administration 
pinochet 74 keeps command of the 60000member army and has 
said he will not permit the new government to prosecute military 
officers for past offenses 
rights organizations and leftist groups many of which supported 
aylwins candidacy are pressing for the trial and punishment of 
offenders 
