<TEXT>
president christos sartzetakis dissolved 
parliament on monday and greeces political parties prepared for 
their third battle after two inconclusive elections since june 
a presidential decree posted next to parliaments entrance 
disbanded the 300member legislature and scheduled elections for 
april 8 
the conservative new democracy party with 148 seats in the last 
