publicsector deficit 
his government succeeded in cutting spending by about 6 billion 
but did not raise revenues 
in june elections new democracy beat former premier andreas 
papandreous panhellenic socialist movement which had been in 
power eight years 
new democracy formed a coalition with the communists and 
indicted papandreou and several other senior socialists on 
corruption charges 
no trial dates were set and a strong showing by the socialists 
in november resulted in new democracy again falling just short of a 
parliamentary majority 
recent opinion polls do not show any significant swing in party 
strengths but new democracy leader constantine mitsotakis says he 
will no longer cooperate with other parties 
you cant wage a battle with three field marshals he told a 
campaign rally on lesbos island sunday 
however the communistled coalition of the left and progress 
reeling after the revolutionary changes in eastern europe has 
indicated it would form an alliance with the socialists 
the communists hinted last weekend they may field joint 
candidates with the socialists in the five singleseat 
constituencies that are traditionally the key to parliamentary 
power 
given present party strengths though a socialistcommunist 
alliance would hold only a slight parliamentary majority such a 
government would have trouble making unpopular decisions 
