los angeles raiders owner al davis said 
monday he wants to bring the national football league team back to 
the city he abandoned eight years ago 
davis breaking a long silence on the issue called local 
officials to lend his support to oaklands offer 
the proposal which guarantees davis raiders 602 million over 
15 years now needs only the approval of the city council and 
alameda county supervisors 
hes ready and were ready said mayor lionel wilson 
this is an eventful day in history for this city 
the separate votes were scheduled for monday night following a 
hearing but the possibility that testimony would be lengthy 
threatened to force a vote postponement 
if davis the raiders managing general partner had said no 
monday or failed to call by a noon deadline the deal would have 
been off 
the nfl formally requires approval by threefourths of team 
owners of any move as well as written notification by jan 15 of 
the year of the proposed relocation but in practice the league 
poses no further obstacles if the city and county approve the offer 
davis moved the raiders from oakland to los angeles without 
permission and won his case in court and robert irsay moved the 
colts without approval from baltimore to indianapolis in 1984 nfl 
owners did approve the 1988 transfer of the cardinals franchise 
from st louis to phoenix 
