proposal was a response to concerns among employees most of the 
newspapers reporters and columnists have withheld their bylines 
from stories since march 7 
they said tell us what you need to remain competitive and 
give us a chance to vote penniman said 
herb goodrick executive secretary of the newspaper guild local 
47 said he would withhold comment until the guild received a 
written version 
