w gold director of labor relations for the news 
the exchange started with a letter from lipton to gold saying 
the guild wanted to terminate its contract such a letter is the 
traditional signal opening a round of contract talks between unions 
and newspapers 
gold confirmed the notice of termination and said the newspaper 
was ready to start collective bargaining for a new contract gold 
also had said that if a new contract was not negotiated by march 
30 the expiration date of the current agreement that contract 
would not be renewed 
the lawsuit said lipton then asked to retract the guilds letter 
requesting termination of the contract and said the union expected 
the terms of the old contract to continue if no agreement was 
reached before march 30 
on feb 15 the guild sent letters to the news and the american 
arbitration association asking for arbitration of the dispute the 
lawsuit said 
the union says it has 799 members at the news 
</TEXT>
