<TEXT>
rorer group inc and frances 
rhonepoulenc sa have signed a 17 billion agreement to create one 
of the worlds largest pharmaceutical companies the companies 
jointly announced monday 
the agreement would combine the surbuban philadelphiabased 
rorer with the parisbased rhonepoulencs human pharmaceutical 
operations in a new firm called rhonepoulenc rorer inc 
the merger is the latest example of consolidation in the drug 
industry and is aimed at lowering research costs and gaining global 
markets 
last year smithkline beckman corp of philadelphia merged with 
britains beecham group plc to form smithkline beecham and 
bristolmyers co of new york acquired squibb corp of princeton 
nj to form bristolmyers squibb co 
the latest transaction will encompass several stages with 
rhonepoulenc initially offering 78 per share for 501 percent of 
rorers 216 million shares a cost of about 842 million 
a tender offer at that price values the entire company at 1685 
billion 
following the tender offer rhonepoulenc will transfer its 
pharmaceuticals business and issue contingent value rights to 
rorer with the number corresponding to nontendered rorer shares 
in exchange rorer will take on 265 million of rhonepoulenc 
debt and acquire the french groups existing us pharmaceutical 
subsidiary for 20 million 
rorer also will create 24 million new shares giving 
rhonepoulenc 68 percent of rorers share capital comprising some 
673 million shares 
rhonepoulenc expects to acquire the 68 percent of rorer by june 
1990 
the tender offer will begin friday rhonepoulenc said the 
companies had announced their intentions to merge earlier this year 
in trading on the new york stock exchange rorer was the most 
active issue rising 3 a share to 6587 on volume of nearly 23 
million shares 
the agreement does not include other portions of the french 
companys healh business such as serums and vaccines veterinary 
medicines animal nutrition and rhonepoulencs interest in roussel 
uclaf sa 
through rhonepoulenc rorer we will achieve our mission of 
becoming a top 10 researchbased pharmaceutical company said 
robert e cawthorn chairman president and chief executive 
officer of rorer cawthorn has been named to the same positions in 
the new company which will be based in fort washington 
the company expects to have annual sales exceeding 3 billion 
he said 
the human pharmaceutical business of rhonepoulenc had sales of 
19 billion in 1989 while rorer had 12 billion the companies 
said 
analyst ron nordmann of painewebber group inc said it is too 
early to make any judgments on the new company 
in terms of the details the companys potential earning power 
is still up in the air he said we need to get more numbers on 
the company before we are able to do any earnings assessment 
rorer is best known for its maalox antacid rhonepoulenc is in 
the top 10 in the european pharmaceutical market but has no direct 
marketing in the united states or japan 
that french company has no presence in the us then 
overnight they are in said analyst michael martorelli of janney 
montgomery scott inc in philadelphia and rorer gets the french 
companys drugs and adds somebody elses research to it own 
he said the merger kills any takeover rumors swirling around 
rorer 
now with a large partner theyll no longer be subject to the 
rumors he said management can stop worrying about that it 
seemed like everytime they turned around there was another takeover 
rumor or question 
