<TEXT>
nortek inc has reached a settlement 
with the securities and exchange commission over a dispute 
involving a fourday delay in filing a form with the government 
disclosing its investment in another company 
nortek said it agreed to a consent decree under which it will 
pay 503000 into a fund to reimburse any rexham corp stockholders 
who may have lost money as a result of the delay in notifying the 
sec of its investment 
the incident occurred more than three years ago 
richard j harris nortek vice president and treasurer said his 
company purchased more than 5 percent of the outstanding shares of 
rexham in 1986 
the sec said nortek delayed by four days filing a form that 
detailed the purchase as is required when a company or individual 
buys more than 5 percent of another company 
nortek filed an untimely false and misleading statement of 
its rexham investment said mary mccue of the sec nortek had 
purchased 62000 shares of rexham stock in 1986 but a form the 
company filed with the sec did not disclose properly norteks 
position and their intent regarding rexham ms mccue said 
nortek sold its investments in rexham of pineville nc in 
1987 harris said 
nortek neither admitted nor denied that it had broken any laws 
or regulations as a result of its rexham investment he said it 
agreed to the settlement to close the case and avoid further legal 
expenses he said 
under the terms of the judgment filed in federal court monday 
any rexham stockholders who sold shares during the fourday period 
and who lost money can seek repayment through the fund nortek is 
establishing any money that is not claimed will revert to the us 
treasury 
nortek filed its consent to a proposed judgment in order to 
bring an end to the continuous drain on management time and to 
avoid incurring additional legal fees said ralph r pappito 
chairman and chief executive officer we are pleased to put this 
bit of our history behind us 
harris said he did not know how much in interest will be paid by 
nortek 
